---
import Section from "./Section.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import chupacabra from "../assets/chupacabra.jpg";
---

<Section title="Cryptid of the Month">
  <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-xs shadow-md">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6">
      <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 bg-white rounded-xs drop-shadow-md p-4">
        <Image 
          src={chupacabra} 
          alt="Chupacabra" 
          width={400} 
          height={300} 
          class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="w-full md:w-2/3">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-2 font-mono uppercase">Chupacabra</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">First reported in Puerto Rico in 1995, the Chupacabra (Spanish for 'goat-sucker') is known for attacking and drinking the blood of livestock. Described as a reptilian creature with leathery skin, spikes down its back, and glowing red eyes, sightings have spread throughout Latin America and the southern United States.</p>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <a href="/files" class="text-blue-900 font-mono hover:underline hover:drop-shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(30,58,138,0.5)] transition-all">View all cryptid files →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
